
// -------------------------------------------------------
//         EVALUATION OF THE BESSEL FUNCTION
// ------------------------------------------------------

INPUTS ; 
x = the value of the varaible in the Bessel function
n = power of x/2 in the Bessel function
tol = tolerance of the error in the Bessel power expansion

// -------------------------------------------------------
// 		       DESCRIPTION
// -------------------------------------------------------

the computation of the Bessel term has been divided in three
parts:
(x/2)^n/n! =(x/2)/1 * (x/2)/2 * .... * (x/2)/n
(x/2)^m/m! =(x/2)/1 * (x/2)/2 * .... * (x/2)/m
(x/2)^m/   =(x/2)/(n+1) * (x/2)/(n+2) * ...* (x/2)/(n+m)

// --------------------------------------------------------
// 			OUPUTS
// --------------------------------------------------------
m = number of summands in the power expansion with the requiered precision
tol = tolerance requiered
value = value of the Bessel function.

// ------------------------------------------------------------------------
// RUNNING THE MAKE FILE
// ------------------------------------------------------------------------
 // make run


